To install vim, download the source,
$ ./configure
$ make
$ sudo make install.

If you want to install it locally, do
$ ./configure --prefix=$HOME/pkg
$ make
$ make install

If you need additional packages (try `vim --version` to see what packages you already have), use e.g.
$ ./configure --prefix=$HOME/pkg --with-x --enable-pythoninterp
$ make
$ make install
this would add the python interpretor and xterm_clipboard

Try ./configure --help
